      "side": 1,
      "message": "This seems pretty straight forward, so I\u0027m not sure what\u0027s causing the issues with the chrome layout tests. It is striking that the failures all appear to be ignoring a round-rect clip mask in the compositor. These are handled here, I believe: https://source.chromium.org/chromium/chromium/src/+/master:components/viz/service/display/skia_renderer.cc;drc\u003d03100289feba14f83a674a43a56da480ba8d2ed2;l\u003d1106\n\nIt doesn\u0027t seem to be a general issue with backdrop filtering, since plenty of tests in chrome still pass that don\u0027t have this backdrop. I think these all go through this since the others are canvas related, but alternatively could be clipped via https://source.chromium.org/chromium/chromium/src/+/master:components/viz/service/display/skia_renderer.cc;drc\u003d03100289feba14f83a674a43a56da480ba8d2ed2;l\u003d999\n\nThose don\u0027t rely on drawSpecial/drawDevice to my knowledge, so I\u0027m not sure what\u0027s going on, and I\u0027m not sure why changing how we\u0027d do filtering would mess up later draws into them. ",
